<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1436,1655,2016]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Diagnosis: Surstyli asymmetrical, OS with a pointed tip in dorsal view; epandrium elongated. SES with hairy ridges on both sides; gonopods short, both with medial lobes (overlapping in ventral view), IG with pointed tip; phallic guide broad, sides parallel, distal part with three pointed appendices; phallus trifid, coiled.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
